ierung und Umwertung von Bauten -- tChanging Content, Shifting Meaning Ottoman Value Attributions to Hagia Eirene in Istanbul -- tShifting Values around the (Non-)Existence of the Historical Artillery Barracks at Taksim-Gezi, Istanbul -- tMonumentalising the Present The Case of the Atatürk Cultural Centre -- tBitte umwerten Zu nationalsozialistischen Monumentalanlagen nach 19450 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aInnerhalb von Entwurfs-, Planungs- und Bauprozessen finden stetig Neu- und Umwertungen statt. Jede zu treffende Entscheidung greift dabei auf bestehende Referenzwerte zurück, auch wenn das jeweilige Handeln zukunftsorientiert und auf das Schaffen des Neuen hin ausgerichtet ist. Zugleich liegen dem Erhalt oder der Weiterentwicklung baulicher Gefüge tradierte Denkmuster und kontinuierlich verinnerlichte Wertesysteme zu Grunde. Dies alles bedeutet: Werte sind auch im Bauen niemals statisch, sondern unterliegen einem Prozess. Im Fokus dieses Bandes und seiner interdisziplinär angelegten Beiträge stehen Vorgänge der Wertaneignung, Wertverinnerlichung und Wertbildung: Sie werden an ausgewählten Beispielen der Bau- und Planungsgeschichte von der Neuzeit bis zur Gegenwart anschaulich gemacht.  aWithin the architectural design, planning, and construction processes, new valuations and revaluations are constantly taking place. Every decision is made based on existing reference values, even if the respective action is future-oriented and geared towards the creation of the new. At the same time, the preservation or further development of building structures is based on traditional thought patterns and continuously internalized value systems. This means that values are never static, even in building, but are subject to a process. This interdisciplinary volume focuses on processes of value appropriation, value internalization, and value formation. These processes are illustrated using selected examples from the history of building and planning from modern times to the present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aARCHITECTURE / History / General.2bisacsh1 aAr, Bilge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeyenbach, Luisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhatawadekar, Shraddha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDinler, Mesut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEss, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEss, Julia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFroschauer, Eva Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFroschauer, Eva Maria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHahn, Achim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerold, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKibel, Jochen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKüçük, Zeynep, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeier, Hans-Rudolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReimersdahl, Marcus van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichter, Elke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichter, Elke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoos, Dorothea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöger, Moritz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaner, Turgut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchulte, Clara Jiva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchul